name: FEATURE_LAST_DIR
de: Change back to last directory
see: CD CHDIR CDD PUSHD POPD
req:

DESCRIPTION:

If defined on compilation of FreeCOM, every change of the current
directory using an internal command records the previous directory
and enables the <ARG>-</ARG> shortcut for CD, CDD and CHDIR.

EXAMPLE:
CMD: C> CD \
CMD: C> CD freedos\bin
CMD: C> CD -
CMD: C> CD -
<BR>The first CD command changes into the root direcotry, the second into
the directory <TT>\FREEDOS\BIN</TT>, any subsequent <CMD>CD -</CMD> commands
will change between the root directory and <TT>\FREEDOS\BIN</TT>.
